<resolution-body style="multiple-resolved-clause" id="H2399A3544723416A9615661B9B650913"> 
<section display-inline="yes-display-inline" section-type="undesignated-section" id="H8217C4BCDE674B2AA38052870EA1C4B6"><text display-inline="yes-display-inline">That the House has heard with profound sorrow of the death of the Honorable Richard B. Cheney, a former Vice President of the United States of America.</text></section> <section id="HA713163B39DE45F788FD045712FBC6CC" section-type="resolved"><text>That the Clerk communicate these resolutions to the Senate and transmit a copy thereof to the family of the deceased.</text></section>
<section id="H49F34F072B204298BC814EF5217C46B5" section-type="resolved"><text>That when the House adjourns today, it adjourn as a further mark of respect to the memory of the deceased.</text></section> </resolution-body> <attestation><attestation-group><attestor display="no">Kevin F. McCumber,</attestor><role>Clerk.</role></attestation-group></attestation> </resolution> 

